BeforeOperationEvent

public BeforeOperationEvent(long timestamp,
                            long traceId,
                            int orderIndex,
                            String operationSignature,
                            String classSignature)
This constructor uses the given parameters to initialize the fields of this record.

Parameters:
timestamp - The timestamp of this record.
traceId - The trace ID.
orderIndex - The order index.
operationSignature - The operation signature. This parameter can be null.
classSignature - The class signature. This parameter can be null.

BeforeOperationEvent

public BeforeOperationEvent(Object[] values)
This constructor converts the given array into a record. It is recommended to use the array which is the result of a call to toArray().

Parameters:
values - The values for the record.
Method Detail

toArray

public Object[] toArray()
This method should deliver an array containing the content of the record. It should be possible to convert this array later into a record again.

Returns:
An array with the values of the record.
